  <title translate="true">Salinity of Applied Water Pane</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Salinity of Applied Water Pane</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">This pane is on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Farm_Crop_Properties_Dialog_Bo" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Farm Land Use Properties</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">CROP_SALINITY_APPLIED_WATER is the extra water that must be applied to the crop in units of L</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super;" translate="true">3</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">/T (model units). Its result is added to the crops &quot;ADDED_DEMAND&quot; to include its irrigation as a salt flush. To force all the water into the ground, you must specify the WBS Block </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="FMP-Farm-Process-V4" anchor="Added_Demand_Runoff_Split" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">ADDED_DEMAND_RUNOFF_SPLIT</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> close to Zero</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">RHOADES Equation ==&gt; (ETi/DU)/(1-LR) - ETi</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><snippet src="CROP_LEACHING_REQUIREMENT-and-" inline="false"/></para>
